31. Scytala. At Sparta, when the magistrates gave commis· sion to any commender of the fleet or army, they took two round straight sticks, exactly alike3 keeping one themselves, and giving the ‘other to the commender: and when they wished to make any communication to him, they cut a long narrow strap from a skin, and wrapping it around their own stick, in such manner that the edges should exactly meet, they wrote upon it what they desired; then taking it off, sent it to him.
